      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe add before/after checks for _INC_MATH to make sure it wasn\u0027t and then is defined, since we depend on that elsewhere.\n\nAlso, has copying the necessary definitions here been considered?  Copying the function prototypes is ugly, but so is #define __inline. I know that VC++ detects and rejects using #define on some C/C++ keywords and they may extend that detection to __inline at some point.",
